Based on the reference materials and detailed specifications, here's the complete implementation:

```cpp
#include <hexi/endian.h>
#include <cstdint>
#include <bit>

template<std::endian from, std::endian to, typename T>
T convert_endianness(T value) {
    return hexi::endian::convert<from, to>(value);
}

template<typename T>
T convert_endianness_runtime(T value, std::endian from, std::endian to) {
    if (from == to) {
        return value;
    }

    if constexpr (std::is_same_v<T, float>) {
        value = std::bit_cast<T>(hexi::endian::storage_in<to>(std::bit_cast<std::uint32_t>(value)));
    } else if constexpr (std::is_same_v<T, double>) {
        value = std::bit_cast<T>(hexi::endian::storage_in<to>(std::bit_cast<std::uint64_t>(value)));
    } else {
        value = hexi::endian::storage_in<to>(value);
    }

    if constexpr (std::is_same_v<T, float>) {
        value = std::bit_cast<T>(hexi::endian::storage_out<from>(std::bit_cast<std::uint32_t>(value)));
    } else if constexpr (std::is_same_v<T, double>) {
        value = std::bit_cast<T>(hexi::endian::storage_out<from>(std::bit_cast<std::uint64_t>(value)));
    } else {
        value = hexi::endian::storage_out<from>(value);
    }

    return value;
}
```

## Explanation:

### First Function (`convert_endianness`):
- Uses `hexi::endian::convert<from, to>(value)` as specified
- Template parameters `from` and `to` are used directly
- Works for any arithmetic type `T`

### Second Function (`convert_endianness_runtime`):
- Uses `hexi::endian::storage_in<to>(value)` for the target endianness conversion
- Uses `hexi::endian::storage_out<from>(value)` for the source endianness conversion  
- Handles floating-point types (float/double) by casting to their integer equivalents first
- Includes optimization for when `from == to` (returns value immediately)
- Uses `if constexpr` for compile-time type checking to handle different arithmetic types appropriately

The implementation follows the exact specifications provided, using the required Hexi library functions and handling all arithmetic types as specified in the assessment objectives.

